data: This is gonna be the decoy van.
This van's the wrong color, Forbes.
Relax. It's nothing a little paint can't fix.
This van is good to Van Gogh... Heh-heh.
Yeah, funny... Vic, take the decoy and lead the cops away from here.
We'll let you know when we're home free.
Uh, yeah - we're on our way. Keep the cops busy.
We're nearly there. Just a little longer.
We're there! Ten-Ten, let's do it again, big cowboy.
Lose the smokey Vic. You're all done.
Lance has made it back to the lockup! Lose the cops!
'Course - you can't kid a kidder. Hey, Vic...
So, Vic, wanna hear about a little plan that is going to make us three very rich?
Let me put it like this - you will not be handling any drugs.
All I need you to do is keep the cops busy
while Lance and I steal some merch, off the scum who brought it into this country.
The drugs're already here. So we ain't drug trafficking.
You're just the decoy - all you gotta do is make the police think you're carrying.
They can't arrest you for that.
No, but they can shoot me.
Yeah. Come on man! Come on.
Vic - you'll be fine... rich and fine!
The cops are on to you. Don't lose your wanted level.
So, you want Information... and what better source than a cop, right?
Hey Vic. See... great minds think alike...
Yeah, fools seldom differ, dip shit.
You want info? How about this?
There's a dealer's boat mooring up Downtown today. The dealer's not the trusting kind, and he'll only meet one-on-one.
He's carrying money and coke, and he doesn't believe in bodyguards.
If I'm lying, genius, I'm a dead man, right?
I'll meet this guy, Vic. You can watch over me,
and I'll see you down there.
Lance has been taken aboard that ship. Rescue him.
I thought this guy didn't use bodyguards.
Forbes's info is seriously out of date.
I'll get us some transport, you get what we came for,
and I'll meet you on shore.
Hey! Make sure no one can see it back there.
The sooner I off-load this coke the better.
This junk heap ain't doing my image any favors.
Don't get too far away or you will lose them.
Yeah yeah yeah, I was going to tell you about that...
The contact is at the White Stallionz bar.
You better not be screwing us.
Me? Gimme a break... I'm your best buddy.
Something's not right about this place...
Yeah! I didn't know bikers were into disco...
I think Forbes has fucked us again.
I wanna bareback the little one.
Man, Forbes screwed us again. Let's get back and screw HIM...
Aw man, I didn't mean for us to kill him.
It's a little late now, Lance!
I know there was something to this big shipment he was talking about.
And I'm going to find out.
They'll give you exactly what you need.
Aaw, shit... it's two for one at the boy's club.. shit.
I know there's a major shipment coming in real soon. I've been to your apartment and I've read your files...
Regard this as a down-payment on your services. I'll be in touch.
Ah, Vic... I hope you play golf.
Sure, I've played a round or two.
I play around all the time - but don't tell my wife.
Vic, I find the way a man plays golf says much about him.
Si. For instance - I trusted Jesus over there, yet he betrayed me.
I should have known better, he's a terrible golfer.
Let's see if I like the way you play, ah?
I've a deal coming up very soon Vic...
Bueno! You bastard! No one sells me out!
Let's just say I'd rather my boss didn't find out about this... or my men, for that matter.
Let me guess - you've cut your Colonel's coke to make a side profit...
This is after all the land of opportunity.
I don't care who you rip off Gonzalez, as long as it's not me.
Bueno. The drugs are at Ocean Beach... Take them to the deal in Washington.
You hit the van too hard: the drugs have gone everywhere. There's more on this dude than in the back.
Quit whining. Let's just get this shit up to the party on Starfish. We've got bitches waiting.
Gonzalez? We got hit... The drugs... They're gone...
What? Are you fucking with me?
What's wrong with you? Are you high on my shit?
No... yeah... I must've been breathing it in while I was out cold.
I want my drugs back Vic. I still have a buyer who might be interested, but he's leaving town real soon.
Kill the bastards who did this and get my drugs back to the lock up.
Well, at least you managed to retrieve my merchandise ... but I think, for our friendship, this is the end.
Ah, Vic, my friend. I've a small side deal requiring a... sensitive touch.
Take the guns back to your Colonel. But, remember, you belong to me now.
Any shipments you bring to Vice City come through me.
Vic. I was just talking to my new friend Gonzalez about loyalty.
How I will look after him so long as he does what he's told.
And you will do as you're told won't you!
Bueno. Escort him to the airport Vic.
Show him what it means to be a friend of Ricardo Diaz... and what it is to be an enemy.
Vic Vance reporting for duty sir.
Ha ha ha! Relax, relax. Are you well?
Good. In here, you can call me Jerry.
Now, Vic, tell me... why did you sign up, huh?
Because you like getting shouted at, huh?
What makes you polish your boots and put bullets in your gun
in the hopes that maybe you'll get to shoot someone, huh? Ha ha ha!
I got a difficult family. I got responsibilities.
What, kids? A broad giving you shit?
One is real sick, asthma, and I gotta pay the bills,
the other, well, maybe he's sick too, but in a different way...
So, you joined the army... to get rich?
Not exactly. But y'know, my dad he came here from DR, we didn't have a lot of opportunities.
What else was I supposed to do? Why did you join up?
Why are you messing with me, sergeant?
I ain't. Chill. Relax. Take a seat. Look, Vic.
There are plenty of opportunities for a man who knows the game to make real money. So...
I don't want any trouble, man.
Who wants trouble? Nobody. Everybody wants to relax. No trouble.
Listen, I don't think this is for me. So, if there's nothing else...
Hey, relax, huh? Come on Vic. I need a favor. No risk.
So why do you need me if there's no risk?
Because I gotta take registration. Besides, you're not on duty for a couple of days.
Listen, you take my bike, you go over to the airport and you pick up a package for me, huh?
Okay, just this one favor and that's it.
And there's plenty of money to be made. Nice and easy.
Come with me soldier. I've got something for your boss.
Man, life's been good to you.
Hm hmm... Come on. Let's take a ride.
Tell him my cut goes up next time.
Vice City's getting too peligroso for us freelancers...
Speaking of which... we've got company.
Grab that gun and take them out.
Listen, if plans change, I'll let you know.
Yeah, well, funny thing, you see, it's like this...
It's under the floorboards at my old place.
Sure. No worries. Oh, look, I gotta go. The cavalry just turned up. OK, bye. Corporal, what can I do for you?
Listen, Jerry, you gotta get rid of that stuff. It's making me nervous.
I'm not into drugs, and I don't...
Chill the fuck out, my friend. You're really getting on my nerves.
Besides, who are you going to get in trouble with? I'm your superior officer...
And you told me you needed the money.
Uh-huh! But you don't like drugs?
I don't think they're a good scene.
Me neither. But you like guns, huh? They don't give you a moral problem I mean?
Good, cause I know a guy who can sell all the guns we can get him. Which is, trust me, quite a lot.
I don't know Sergeant, this is getting heavy.
You'll make a whole pile of cash, for nothing. Buy that sick brother of yours a whole lot of candy.
What do I have to do?
Nothing. Just go and pick up the money from him. He's down over by the docks.
Hey Vic! You want some of this, huh?
But the Cholo evicted me and now I can't get to it.
You must be Vic. Jerry told me about you.
Hey. I used to be in the service...
Yeah, listen, he said you'd have some money for me.
Well, I ain't a bank... I don't have it on me. But I'll take you to it.
I've been having trouble with them Cholo boys. Some of them have been...
What the hell is a Cholo?
Bunch of Mexican Gang-bangers. Bad boys, trying to take over all the gun running in town.
Look, I'm not some idiot that you can just...
I never called you an idiot. Oh, shhh, shhh - look at that - oooh, now she got a pig and a horse. Hooowee! Heh heh.
That's Candy Suxx! He he he! That's some guy's daughter man!
No, you listen, huh? Oh, dude - would you look at that - man - I gotta get laid.
Oh jeez... Hey, if you weren't such a square I'd do you, huh? Ha ha ha! I'm joking! Come on.
This is the army - not the navy, huh? Heh heh heh!
Listen, man, I need a broad, huh? Oh - I need Mary...
I need you to collect your pot, dude.
Sure. I'll go get that from your quarters,
you go get Mary for me, okay? She's over at Viceport.
Oh, and go see Phil again. He said something about a gift for you.
Hey, that is not an appropriate way to speak to a superior officer. Ha ha ha! Now get on with it.
The reefer is under my bed.
Oh, genius! Great hiding place... what are you? 15? Hurry up... oh, hey, tell Mary I love her!
Martinez wanted me to give you this.
Don't worry? Man, I'm getting too deep into this shit.
Did Martinez send you? That cockroach still owes me from last time.
Take it easy, muscles, I've got a delicate disposition.
Corporal Vance! Would you care to explain why there's marijuana hidden under your bed?
And who the Sam Hill is this?
Hey buddy, listen I charge more for groups.
You brought a whore onto the base!
Have you no shame boy! Are you a moron? Is that it?
DRUGS! WHORES! You're out of here soldier! You're a disgrace.
If you want Mary, she's at a party up on Starfish. I'm heading over there myself; you can give me a lift.
If there's anything I can do for you, or to you, just let me know.
Thanks for the ride rugged fella. Maybe I can pay you back in kind later?
I just need to find Mary.
Hey, we've paid for her! She's not going anywhere!
Damn right! C'mon! Let's get this lowlife nobody, and teach this bitch a lesson too!
You can now use Phil's old place as a safehouse.
Any vehicle parked in the garage around the back will be stored whenever you save your game.
Hooo! Hey, Victor Vance! Wow... did anyone ever tell you you've got a really dumb name?
No, no one's ever mentioned that before.
Oh my, look at that... hey, is that legal? Can animals give consent?
I don't know. Listen, Jerry. Can you stash that weed somewhere else?
Ha ha ha! I'm shitting with you, come on! Having fun, rock and roll! Oh, would you fucking relax, my friend?
Mary, yeah, oh, Mary, Mary quite contrary... Ha ha ha! Oh come on man, I need a favor.
I had it wit' you man. You put me off! Always treat me like a kid.
I'd appreciate a ride to my hotel.
Ha ha ha, I wouldn't know. I told them to bill you.
Lance! What are you doing here?
Thanks, bro. Who was you expecting? What a greeting man...
So what am I? A handicap, huh? Your dumb ass, low life, no good brother?
Yeah, well - I'm not the one who got kicked out of the army.
No - you're the asshole who got kicked out of the boy scouts.
Oh come on, man. I come all this way to see you and you treat me like I've got herpes.
Maybe that's because your whole life, you've gotten us into trouble.
Oh, gimme a break, man! I've changed!
Okay. I'll give you a chance. One chance.
Yeah, yeah! Hey, come here man... You won't regret it, baby...
I love you, man, and love can change the world. But Vic...
Get off me man, just get in the damn car.
All the Cholos have been looking for you Mr. Big-Shot.
What do you want with me?
I'm not talking to you. I'm talking to him!
You killed plenty Cholos... Now, we kill you plenty.
Get us out of here Lance!
Is this your idea of a welcome party?
W-wait, where in the hell am I going, man?
I'm just too pretty to die, ha ha ha! Woo!
Look out Vic. There's more of them!
Do you have any friends in this town?
My man's name is Forbes: He's gonna call us at the burger bar any minute now, so let's get down there pronto.
So merchandise is hidden in the car's side panels?
Okay. We're gonna pick up Forbes's car.
Man, give me a break. There's no winning with you.
Aw, shit. You've got to be kidding me.
Man that's just typical! They think we did it!
C'mon. Let's get the car out of here.
I don't get it. How is stealing one dumb car gonna make us rich?
Are there drugs hidden in the car?
Great driving Vic... But, ahm, it's best if I take it from here.
Forbes doesn't know you man... he wouldn't trust you.
I am Lance Vance baby - you can trust me.
Lance T Vance - T for Trust... great. Yeah, love. I love you man!
Vic, look at me. It was nothing.
And you look at me - what was that about?
Like I haven't heard that before. What have you done?
I found a way in - two kids, broken home, no education, no father - and rich as shit.
It's the American dream baby! Pete with good medical treatment.
Listen - I met a big player - and we'll get big money for doing absolutely nothing...
We won't be touching no drugs, man. C'mon! Y'know, I am your brother! You can trust me.
No, not in a funny way... yeah... a'ight... ciao.
We ain't got time for this shit.
Course. Hey, I was just giving you shit, you know?
I need money. I wanna work with you guys... I ain't gonna bust you.
Not now you ain't. I'm gonna bust you!
You're a freaking cop! You think you can mess with Lance T. Vance, you punk?
You got everything sorted? No trouble?
Get him Vic! We gotta find out what he knows.
I got a place we can take him. C'mon.
I don't know about this Lance.
It's either this, or kill him.
Uh, I definitely prefer it this way.
We'll let him sweat for a while.
We'll be back... you sit tight, buddy.
Aw man that's our money! Get him!
What the hell is our money doing in there?
You never know when you're gonna need a few grand...
What the fuck are you talking about?
Isn't that what you guys say? What's popping?
I think that must be Lance.
Yes. You're right, I am a cop. I was gonna tell you.
This guy's a dealer who's getting out of the business. He's getting us a file about this big shipment coming in.
How much is this gonna cost?
You've got to speculate to accumulate. We're Yuppies now, bro...
This dude's plane could be leaving anytime so let's pop, big-time.
You're too late man. I told you - first come first served.
Man that was our file! Who'd you sell it to?
Some dude over at Terminal C.
He's got a private jet... and a private army. I don't think you wanna mess with him.
What the hell are they doing here?
I'm guessing we're not the only ones your contact turned away today.
Hey, Bro'. This cat really knew how to travel. There's some stylish shit in here.
Never mind that. Did you get the file?
No problem? - I could have used a little help out here assbrain!
Take it easy Bro. It's all good.
Lance... take the file and get the hell out of my sight.
Pink. No, blue. No, white - I'll take all three. Hey... I'll call you back!
My problem? My problem is you're going to have us both killed, because you're a moron.
I told you to not get us in so deep.
Oh, shut up and grow some balls.
What, tough guy? What did you say to me? When will you grow a fucking brain?
What are you doing here, mom?
I'm cleaning up my act. I'm off the drugs for good.
That's Javier. He's been very sweet to me...
I'm tired of your bullshit, mom. You've come here to ruin things for us, again.
How can you say that... I raised you.
Aunt Enid raised us, not you.
I'm clean. Give me a chance, Victor - please?
You can stay with Lance, mom - but I don't want any trouble. I've got enough horse shit dealing with him.
Err, Vic, we got to go meet that friend of yours at the airport.
Can I get a drink Lance, honey?
Oh, right... You two, stay out of trouble.
Try to keep up man, I'm a BAAAD driver.
I'm losing you man. Where are you?
Hey, looks like the cops have scared off Martinez...
Thank God almighty, we are rich at last!
We're gonna make it big Vic.
Look, I've even arranged some insurance.
I'll take a look and see what's happening.
You two just sit tight and make sure our exit is clear.
This is about to get ugly.
Take the other truck and follow me.
Looks like your friend Martinez finally showed up...
Rich at last, uh-hu, rich at last, huh...
We haven't sold this shit yet.
We'd better: I've just bought us both fancy apartments. We're mortgaged to the hilt.
We're supposed to be getting out of this shit.
We are. But I gotta do it in style. I've got a reputation to uphold.
Ah! Just in time, bro. Ha ha ha! Yeah!
Lance, I'm through with this, man.
What, you mean this dump? Yeah me too.
No - I'm through with this bullshit. I don't wanna be a damn drug dealer. It's for assholes.
Vic - don't go soft on me now.
I got what we finally needed - I know how we can get our hands on one big shipment, completely free.
We can finally get Pete the health care he needs.
Look Lance, I'm a long way from being a good guy, but drugs just mean trouble.
I agree, man. 100% agree. That's why we gonna get this one big pay day for all the hard work and split.
Oh... fuck it. You know what? Let's do it.
Alright, ladies and gentlemen, that is a real man. Let's pop.
Martinez is bringing in that big ass shipment Forbes was rapping about...We're gonna rip it off.
My man's filming some 'Z' list movie over at the Mall.
They only let him shoot at night so we better get over there pronto.
Hey Spitz. Looking for inspiration? I got all you need.
All I need huh? A stuntman's what I need. We've got to wrap this scene before the mall opens.
Vic can handle your stunts; meanwhile you and I can talk Snow Business.
We got the deal. We're made for life. Let's go pick up the yayo.
Fill the Gore meter by shooting the zombies, dont let the Gore meter empty before the timer runs out.
The Gore meter will slowly empty over time, but will empty faster if any of the zombies get too close.
In this scene the zombies are invading the record store!
Don't let any of the zombies get into the store.
Ah, never mind man, just get the yayo.
Yeah, it's in the spare room. Ha ha ha!
And Mom's stuff is gone too.
Ain't that a bitch! I can't believe she took our coke...
Yeah, so what do we do now, moron?
Wait, wait, let me think... I know we can make it right. We'll just uh... We'll explain things to the Mendez brothers, you know?
Oh yeah, yeah, yeah, I'm sure in between chopping us up
Lance, if we get out of this, I'm gonna kill you.
and feeding us to their dogs, they'll be very understanding.
Hey, Vic. Like the new threads?
I need to use the phone.
...we can pay off the feds, and handle anything the Mendez brothers throw at us.
Thanks for the coke Martinez. Now you know how it feels to get fucked.
Oh, you fucked us both, Vic.
That coke you ripped off belonged to the Mendez brothers: I was just the shepherd.
Now we're all on their shit list - and the only way off is in a fucking bag.
I'm turning states: I'm gonna ruin you, your brother, Mendez, everyone... Happy Holidays.
We don't have to worry about a thing.
Stop yelling at me. It's not my fault.
Yes it is. If you hadn't stolen the Mendezes' coke they wouldn't be attacking all of my businesses.
I'm sick and tired of you blaming me for everything. Now, I'm gonna save 'your' empire - you do what you want.
My name's Lance, you haven't a chance!
Yeah... well, I wouldn't go that far Bro.
We might have won the day here. But we probably got our asses whipped elsewhere.
...Find a way to get outta this man...
Lance. What the fuck is wrong now?
Nothing, nothing at all... we're fine.
Really? 'Cos I tell you something, we don't look fine.
Well let me tell YOU something. We are.
Well, 'we' look like a moron who just realized 'we' just screwed up his entire family!
I am Cool, man. I am relaxed as hell. Yeah.
The Mendez brothers... they don't want us dead anymore.
No. They might want to hurt us a bit, but kill us? Nah...
WHAT HAVE YOU GOTTEN US INTO, YOU DUMB SHIT?
There might be a... little problem...
Your gang are defending all your other businesses for you.
Well speak for your damn self! It's just business, baby. I think I sorted out everything.
Ok, so a pair of homicidal lunatics merely want to hurt me a bit, and I'm actually pleased about it.
No. You can barely tie your own shoelaces, and you're telling me how to behave?
WILL YOU SHUT UP YOU STUPID GORILLA?
THE PLACE IS BUGGED! THE DEA IS ONTO US!
The DEA won't even get a signal from these things.
Collect a free rocket launcher from the shop keeper.
For every antenna you destroy, it takes the DEA longer to collect evidence.
We're gonna have bugs in all our places...
And by the time you've found them all we'll be half way through a long jail term.
What am I supposed to do?
These bugs transmit long range... so knock out all the police antennae.
Lance, get over here and explain yourself.
You've stopped the DEA collecting evidence! Now reduce your wanted level to zero.
The DEA are collecting evidence against you. Hurry up!
Grenades can also be used to destroy antennae.
You do the flying - I'll do the frying, ha ha!
That's it! Run you sissy boys!
Hey Vic! Look what I found.
You're alive! I thought you were dead.
No man. I landed on a few soft bikers. Now I've got me a new bike. Yeah!
Never mind that. Where's the stolen coke?
...ahm, yeah... They probably sold it already. ...The bastards.
I don't even know why I bother sometimes.
Ha ha! Yeah I'm Lance T. Vance, baby!
Oh, bro, that's just the accountant - he's getting us a better rate at cleaning the money.
Well yeah... I'm a friendly guy. And 'baby' is slang, you know? I don't love him. I ain't like that.
Anyway, we got real things to worry about - someone's been helping themselves to the stash...
The Mendezes are freaking out, and I told 'em we'd take care of it.
Ah, that's the last thing I need, on top of everything else.
What are you talking about? What's wrong?
Oh, man, it's just... Louise. I really thought we had something, but we just don't get to see each other.
Yeah, well, y'know, relationships can be tough. Believe me, I know.
You can take out your sexual frustrations on them. Come on! Let's pop!
You know I love you bro. Ay...
'T' for tulips in Thailand. Great. Ha ha! Yeah, look, I gotta go. A'ight. Later.
Come on man, we got some thieves to deal with.
So who's been stealing the yayo?
Well, I guess I'm just gonna have to prove it to you.
I can see a bunch of those ugly mothers down there. Take us in closer. I'm gonna pop a few heads.
Tilting the helicopter will lower Lance's balance.
Lance will stop firing if he loses his balance.
Keeping the helicopter level will improve Lance's aim.
Shut up! You're always telling me what to do. But if it wasn't for me we wouldn't have any of this.
If I wanna take coke, I will. If I wanna give it away, I will...
Alright baby! This is the Lance Vance Dance...
So this is where the coke is going? Up your nose?
You had me running around town like a psycho,
and all the while you're siphoning it off for your personal use. You are unbelievable.
Hey, I'm sorry... uh, look, can we talk about this later?
Louise! What the hell is going on?
Well uh, um... Uh, bro... Eh, eh! Bro, it ain't nothing like that!
I wouldn't do that to you... I just needed something to take my mind off things.
No! We just get high together. God damn, you are so judgmental, like you're a damn saint or something.
Why are you being such an asshole?
And you're wonderful. A wonderful drug dealing, thieving murderer.
I was doing it for us.
Who're you trying to kid? You don't give a shit about me.
You know what? You make me wanna puke, ya self-righteous dick.
Stay away from me you sick bastard. You're a phony, Vic Vance.
What? Listen - who cares? It's my coke, it's all my coke and I'll do with it whatever I damn well please!
You got ta... Pop it... And ah... Lock it... Yeah! Wow!
And I'm gonna give it away! All of it! And you can't stop me!
I need some help over here! Come on, get a doctor.
And because I want to get back together, I'm trying to avoid being killed.
Oh, man. What month is it? Did I do anything stupid in the last few days?
Stupid? Oh no... you passed stupid and kept on going, straight on into fucked up.
Lance? It's Louise. Where's Vic... I need him.
It's me Louise. What is it?
Vic? Oh thank god. It's that Martinez. He must think we're still an item.
For crying out loud Vic, I didn't sleep with Lance. We're just friends, which is more than you've been lately.
You never call. We never see each other.
I just wanted you to know that Martinez's thugs have been following me.
And now I'm hiding out round the back of some stupid Burger Bar. Not that you'd give a shit.
What? Martinez sent guys after you?
I don't even know why I called. I'm gonna kick their asses myself.
Lance, you wanna help me out?
Louise? Hey, Louise? Are you there?
Is that your bitch? ...She's Martinez's now.
Vic. I knew you'd come. I think I need a doctor...
I'll put you ALL in a Lance Vance trance.
C'mon Vic. We've got them on the run.
They're running for it. Time to turn up the pain!
Look at them run! Ha ha ha!
I can't believe it. We're winning.
We rolled over them like a big, bad bowling ball. Let's find another lane of pain. C'mon!
Did you see me taking 'em down?
You're a blidiot. Now shut up.
We've been lucky so far. Stop being such a dick ...'Lance-erator'.
I killed more than you. I should be in charge of this outfit.
Do you know where you're going?
We should be shooting bad guys by now.
I just received a message from Umberto and Phil. They've been kicking asses, just like us.
You mean we did it? We won?
Yeah! The Mendez brothers can kiss my ass. They thought they could take us down.
They're finished. We should take the fight to them.
I heard there was gonna be a party, so I brought fireworks...
There he is... heh heh heh! Mr. Victor Vance the punk who needs our help.
Your brother, man. At least one of you has something up here and a lot down here, huh?
We're about to get hit by those Mendez guys,
thought we could use some of your buddies to crash the party.
Help out... What, did I do wrong again?
No, no, no, no man, for once, you did very right. Let's go deal with these pricks.
Yeah, let's pop! Ha ha haaa!
You grown any cajones yet, lady boy? Come here Vic.
So if you guys are ready, let's do this.
I'm the black killa from Manila! The Manila Blilla!
And I know just the man to make it happen.
We should spread out and cover as much ground as we can.
Let me know if you need any help.
Wait up. I'm gonna need some serious artillery for this gig...
My name is Lance Vance. It's time to dance.
Simon says... eat lead and play dead.
I'm lean and I'm mean and I'm here to clean.
Man, we're the badasses on the block! Let's get to the next ass-kicking.
You need to defend all three businesses before the timer expires. Hurry up!
Do you want to do something fun? No business, just me and you?
What the hell? - 'Trapped in a burning building' - 'Bring a helicopter'.
There's the building. I can't see Lance though... get in closer.
Did you run into any trouble? No. Well I did!
Martinez set us up - Divide and conquer.
Martinez's men took everything. But we're gonna get it back.
They headed out to sea. C'mon, let's get after them.
Yeah, not so clever now, huh!
